%p#mission-statement
  The founding purpose of Ruby Australia is to further the use and adoption of
  the Ruby programming language in Australia, and to support and encourage a
  vibrant community around the language and related technologies.

%section#meetups
  %h3 Meetups
  %p
    There are a number of regional Ruby-related meetups all over the country.
    Each group is organised independently by its members, and all are very
    welcoming to newcomers. The following groups meet regularly:

  %ul.meetup-locations
    %li
      %a#adl{href: '/meetups/adl.html'} Adelaide
    %li
      %a#bne{href: '/meetups/bne.html'} Brisbane
    %li
      %a#can{href: '/meetups/can.html'} Canberra
    %li
      %a#mel{href: '/meetups/mel.html'} Melbourne
    %li
      %a#per{href: '/meetups/per.html'} Perth
    %li
      %a#syd{href: '/meetups/syd.html'} Sydney

